  <h1 class="center">Practice Organization</h1>

  <hr class="light-smoke">

  <div class="center ol-font">by <%= link_to "Coach Hrazor", articles_coach_hrazor_path, class: "dark-red" %></div> 

  <br>

  <p class="art-font">If your budget allows, I recommend purchasing some type of practice segment timer that is programmable, otherwise you will have to use your wristwatch or cell phone as a timekeeper.</p>

  <p class="art-font">Use Definite6 to construct your practice schedule. It’s easy, customizable, and will save you a lot of time. Defininte6 allows you to set-up a default template that can be tailored to fit your needs. The default template will then be used each time you create a new schedule – this allows you to create new practice schedules within minutes. Below is an image of a practice schedule created using Definite6.</p>

  <p class="center art-font"><%= link_to "Sign-up for Definite6 Now!", new_user_registration_path, class: "blue" %></p>
  
  <%= image_tag("PracticeSchedule.png", alt: "Football Practice Schedule", class: "formation-image") %>

  <br>
  <br>

  <p class="art-font">We have a pre-practice time where the team gathers in the end zone for the presentation of daily objectives and points of emphasis. We are off the clock for team dynamic warm up/stretch, and conditioning/water break on the days we condition.  Then we start the clock.</p>

  <p class="art-font">Practice begins when the segment timer horn sounds.  We use 25 five-minute periods and alter the content of the periods depending on the day.</p>

  <p class="art-font">In general, our daily practice plan includes the following periods:</p>

  <ul class="art-font">
    <li>Individual Special Team Skills/Techniques</li>
    <li>Team Special-Teams Reps</li>
    <li>Individual Position Skills/Techniques/Methods</li>
    <li>Position Group(s) Assignment/Recognition Reps</li>
    <li>Routes vs Air</li>
    <li>7 on 7</li>
    <li>Inside Run</li>
    <li>Goal Line (5 yds and in)</li>
    <li>Team:</li>
      <ul class="nested-list">
        <li>Specific Pass Reps</li>
        <li>Run Game Classification, e.g., Zone Period, Counter Period, Jet Sweep Period</li>
        <li>Down/Distance Situation</li>
        <li>Field Position Situation</li>
        <li>Time Remaining Situation</li>
      </ul>
  </ul>

